Privacy Policy for PromptR
Last Updated: April 25, 2026

The PromptR Team ("we," "our," or "us") is committed to protecting your privacy. This Privacy Policy explains how we collect, use, and disclose information when you use our mobile application, PromptR.

1. Information We Collect
PromptR is designed to be a "local-first" tool.

Personal Data: We do not collect personally identifiable information (PII) such as your name, email address, or phone number unless you explicitly provide it to us for support purposes.

Camera Data: PromptR requires access to your device’s camera to provide the teleprompter overlay feature. We do not record, stream, or store your camera feed. The camera feed is processed locally on your device in real-time to allow you to see your scripts while speaking.

2. Permissions
To provide our services, we request the following permissions:

Camera: Used strictly for the teleprompter overlay functionality.

Storage/Media: Used to save and load your speech scripts on your device.

3. Data Storage and Security
All scripts and settings created within PromptR are stored locally on your device. We do not transmit your scripts or camera data to external servers. We implement industry-standard security measures to protect any information you may provide to us via support channels.

4. Third-Party Services
We do not sell, trade, or otherwise transfer your information to outside parties. We do not use third-party tracking or advertising SDKs that monitor your behavior.

5. Children’s Privacy
Our services do not address anyone under the age of 13. We do not knowingly collect personally identifiable information from children under 13.

6. Changes to This Policy
We may update our Privacy Policy from time to time. We will notify you of any changes by posting the new Privacy Policy on this page and updating the "Last Updated" date.

